WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:04.460
[ Siren wails, horns honking ]

00:04.460 --> 00:06.670
Meredith: In 1967,
surgeons in South Africa

00:06.670 --> 00:08.670
performed the first successful
heart transplant.

00:08.670 --> 00:11.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:11.040 --> 00:12.540
The following year,

00:12.540 --> 00:16.420
there were 100 heart
transplants worldwide.

00:16.420 --> 00:19.040
Problem was,
the patients kept dying.

00:19.040 --> 00:20.960
I told you I didn't want
to have a party.

00:20.960 --> 00:22.620
♪ I can already tell ♪

00:22.620 --> 00:24.000
[ Siren wailing ]

00:24.000 --> 00:25.380
♪ I'm under your spell ♪

00:25.380 --> 00:27.830
So the following year,
transplants fell to 18.

00:27.830 --> 00:32.000
♪ And that spells trouble,
trouble for me ♪

00:32.000 --> 00:34.620
Kinda seems like people were a
little too eager to celebrate.

00:34.620 --> 00:36.170
♪ I can't get it off my mind ♪

00:36.170 --> 00:40.790
Wow, I think that you have found
every egg roll in Seattle.

00:40.790 --> 00:42.920
Well, Mom said nothing
too fancy.

00:42.920 --> 00:44.830
Damn it.
What?

00:44.830 --> 00:46.960
I was just trying to get this
thing to stand up straight.

00:46.960 --> 00:49.080
Oh. Just, um, pour some
of the wax down into the bottom

00:49.080 --> 00:50.500
and then
stick the candle in.

00:50.500 --> 00:53.250
♪ La la la la la la ♪
Right.

00:53.250 --> 00:56.250
This place looks amazing.

00:56.250 --> 00:58.330
Your mother
is going to love this.

00:58.330 --> 00:59.460
She'd better love it.

00:59.460 --> 01:01.790
God knows she gave me
enough stipulations.

01:01.790 --> 01:04.210
No more than 40 people,
no foundation people...

01:04.210 --> 01:05.670
[ Chuckles ]
...no photographers.

01:05.670 --> 01:08.500
"Only the doctors
that saved my life

01:08.500 --> 01:09.830
and a few friends,
child."

01:09.830 --> 01:11.670
[ Chuckles ]
Got it!

01:11.670 --> 01:15.330
♪♪

01:15.330 --> 01:17.170
Oh, my.
[ Chuckles ]

01:17.170 --> 01:18.120
Wow.
♪ Oh, you look so good ♪

01:18.120 --> 01:19.920
[ Chuckles ]

01:19.920 --> 01:21.080
♪ I bet you feel good, too ♪

01:21.080 --> 01:22.380
You know...

01:22.380 --> 01:26.040
people aren't really gonna
be here for a while.

01:26.040 --> 01:27.170
So, I don't see
why we can't...

01:27.170 --> 01:28.920
Uh, there are people
working here.

01:28.920 --> 01:30.420
They'll know.

01:30.420 --> 01:31.750
Well, let them know.

01:31.750 --> 01:33.330
♪ You got that oooh la la la
la la la ♪

01:33.330 --> 01:34.670
You're coming with me.
[ Chuckles ]

01:34.670 --> 01:36.330
♪ You got that oooh la la la
la la la ♪

01:36.330 --> 01:37.330
Bye. [ Chuckles ]

01:37.330 --> 01:38.540
[ Clears throat ]

01:38.540 --> 01:40.960
♪ And it's just
the kinda trouble ♪

01:40.960 --> 01:42.960
♪ I've been lookin' for ♪

01:47.460 --> 01:51.460
[ Siren wails, horn honking ]

01:51.460 --> 01:53.080
Diagnostics, please.

01:53.080 --> 01:54.790
Oh, good.
You are still here.

01:54.790 --> 01:56.330
Let's go.
T-- Oh.

01:56.330 --> 01:58.250
Do you need a ride
to your own party?

01:58.250 --> 01:59.750
It's Jackson's party.

01:59.750 --> 02:01.080
And, no,
I don't need a ride.

02:01.080 --> 02:03.710
What I need is a drink
to help calm my nerves...

02:03.710 --> 02:05.580
[ Scoffs ]
...before I have to go
and pretend to like it.

02:05.580 --> 02:07.580
A friend would help.
[ Sighs ]

02:07.580 --> 02:09.120
What?

02:09.120 --> 02:11.620
Okay, I have been
sternly warned,

02:11.620 --> 02:14.460
by more than one person,
not to aid and abet in any way,

02:14.460 --> 02:15.960
should you try to ditch.

02:15.960 --> 02:18.080
Well, I was offering you
a ride in my limousine,

02:18.080 --> 02:20.120
that has a fully
stocked bar.

02:20.120 --> 02:21.790
But enjoy going
in your own car,

02:21.790 --> 02:23.460
that you have to drive
yourself.

02:23.460 --> 02:26.330
You should have led
with limo.

02:26.330 --> 02:28.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:30.500 --> 02:32.380
So, I'm not sure
where it's going,

02:32.380 --> 02:34.750
um [clears throat]
if it's even going anywhere.

02:34.750 --> 02:37.670
But seeing how half of my
co-workers will be at the party

02:37.670 --> 02:40.920
and see us together,
I am doing the responsible thing

02:40.920 --> 02:43.040
and letting you know that
Andrew DeLuca and I are dating.

02:48.000 --> 02:49.960
Well?
Are you telling me this

02:49.960 --> 02:51.580
as the chief
or as your friend?

02:51.580 --> 02:53.620
I don't know.
Both. Why?

02:53.620 --> 02:55.540
Because I want to know if
I need to explain hospital rules

02:55.540 --> 02:56.880
or just laugh at you.

02:58.580 --> 03:00.420
When is Bailey
getting her job back?

03:00.420 --> 03:01.920
Oh, why?
Would you rather tell her?

03:01.920 --> 03:03.460
[ Laughs ] Can I watch?

03:03.460 --> 03:04.960
You know,
you married a resident,

03:04.960 --> 03:06.380
and I didn't say anything.

03:06.380 --> 03:07.620
Yes, you did.

03:07.620 --> 03:10.000
You were mean to her
for like two years.

03:10.000 --> 03:12.880
And by the time I married her,
she was a fellow.

03:12.880 --> 03:15.250
Well, you put my resident
in the hospital.
Okay, we can stop.

03:15.250 --> 03:17.080
But as chief,
I need to tell you

03:17.080 --> 03:19.250
to report your relationship
to HR.

03:19.250 --> 03:22.620
As your friend,
I hope he makes you happy.

03:22.620 --> 03:23.880
Thank you.

03:26.960 --> 03:28.540
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Lawrence to the NICU.

03:28.540 --> 03:31.120
Dr. Lawrence to the NICU.

03:31.120 --> 03:33.330
Chief, Mrs. Karev
wants to see you.

03:33.330 --> 03:34.670
All right, tell her
I'll see her at the party.

03:34.670 --> 03:36.330
And it's Dr. Karev, Helm.

03:36.330 --> 03:38.710
Oh. Right. Sorry.

03:38.710 --> 03:40.250
[ Footsteps ]

03:40.250 --> 03:42.000
He said he'll meet you
at the party.

03:42.000 --> 03:43.040
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

03:43.040 --> 03:44.330
Helen: Oh.

03:44.330 --> 03:46.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:46.670 --> 03:48.580
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Millicent, call Radiology.

03:48.580 --> 03:51.170
Dr. Millicent, call Radiology.

03:51.170 --> 03:52.330
[ Telephone rings in distance,
conversations continue ]

03:56.540 --> 03:57.670
[ Leo crying ]

03:57.670 --> 03:59.120
That's it.

03:59.120 --> 04:01.670
Easy.
It's only been two weeks.

04:01.670 --> 04:03.540
I can get this.
Or you could not.

04:03.540 --> 04:04.920
I could stay.

04:04.920 --> 04:06.750
Betty, you can do this.
How?

04:06.750 --> 04:10.500
I'm a drug addict with a baby
and a dead boyfriend.

04:10.500 --> 04:12.920
I have nothing in common
with anyone my age,

04:12.920 --> 04:15.250
and they're all gonna look at me
like I'm some sort of freak.

04:15.250 --> 04:17.540
Because that's what I am.

04:17.540 --> 04:18.620
I ruined my life.

04:18.620 --> 04:20.120
That was the drugs.

04:20.120 --> 04:22.080
And they tried to ruin
your life, but they failed.

04:22.080 --> 04:23.790
[ Sighs ]
Because you are here.

04:23.790 --> 04:25.250
And I am here,

04:25.250 --> 04:27.420
and I am here for you
no matter where you live.

04:27.420 --> 04:30.330
And you are gonna call me
anytime you need to.

04:30.330 --> 04:32.380
Day or night.
You are not in this alone.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.210
It is gonna get better,
Betty.

04:35.210 --> 04:38.420
I promise you
it gets so much better.

04:38.420 --> 04:39.540
[ Crying continues ]

04:39.540 --> 04:41.620
Can't we just stay another
night, John?

04:41.620 --> 04:43.380
And get stuck
in morning traffic.

04:43.380 --> 04:45.620
Yeah. But -- But it's
4 1/2 hours' difference --

04:45.620 --> 04:47.210
the difference
that's gonna make.

04:47.210 --> 04:49.120
I mean, it's --
it's crazy.
[ Cries loudly ]

04:49.120 --> 04:51.210
Well...
Uh, uh...

04:51.210 --> 04:53.460
[ Lowered voice ]
Sorry, sorry. Uh, just --

04:53.460 --> 04:56.920
Babies are a lot more work
than I remember.

04:56.920 --> 04:59.330
[ Crying continues ]

04:59.330 --> 05:01.960
-[ Sighs ]
-Well, uh...

05:03.920 --> 05:05.750
[ Crying continues ]

05:05.750 --> 05:07.710
God, you're so weird.

05:07.710 --> 05:09.880
[ Crying continues ]

05:09.880 --> 05:11.710
[ Door opens ]

05:11.710 --> 05:14.290
[ Coos, whines ]

05:14.290 --> 05:15.250
[ Crying ]

05:15.250 --> 05:17.120
Well, uh,
thank you both.

05:18.420 --> 05:20.620
So much.

05:20.620 --> 05:22.330
For everything.

05:22.330 --> 05:25.080
[ Crying continues ]

05:25.080 --> 05:27.330
[ Insects chirping in distance ]

05:34.620 --> 05:36.210
She didn't say goodbye.

05:38.580 --> 05:39.920
[ Sighs softly ]

05:39.920 --> 05:41.380
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:41.380 --> 05:43.040
I'm gonna go get ready.

05:43.040 --> 05:45.580
You're going
to the party?

05:45.580 --> 05:47.880
Yeah, I, uh, can't be
in this house tonight.

05:51.040 --> 05:52.920
[ Doorbell chimes ]

05:52.920 --> 05:54.500
Hey, hey.
Hey, hey.

05:54.500 --> 05:56.540
Oh. You know the party's
catered, right?

05:56.540 --> 05:57.880
Well, it's rude not
to bring anything.

05:57.880 --> 05:59.960
Hey! [ Chuckles ]

05:59.960 --> 06:02.670
I rest my case.

06:02.670 --> 06:04.250
Hey, Pierce!

06:04.250 --> 06:05.790
Hi -- Uh, nothing.
[ Scoffs ]

06:05.790 --> 06:07.120
Hi, I mean.

06:07.120 --> 06:08.580
Did you see it?
What?

06:08.580 --> 06:10.420
What? That lady you hated
wrote an article about you.

06:10.420 --> 06:11.750
I'll text it to all of you.

06:11.750 --> 06:13.120
Oh, what lady?
Kiki?
[ Cellphones chime ]

06:13.120 --> 06:15.920
-What kind of article?
-Uh, who is this person?

06:15.920 --> 06:18.460
"How Bravery and Self-Advocacy
Saved My Life."

06:18.460 --> 06:20.420
[ Crunches ]
Oh, that sounds nice.

06:20.420 --> 06:21.960
That bitch.

06:21.960 --> 06:23.170
Why? What'd she say?

06:23.170 --> 06:25.500
Shh, shh, shh.
I'm reading.

06:25.500 --> 06:26.960
I thought you gave
all your money away.

06:26.960 --> 06:29.170
I could fit my whole loft
inside your fireplace.

06:29.170 --> 06:30.830
That's not how it works.

06:30.830 --> 06:32.750
Um, I created
a restricted endowment

06:32.750 --> 06:34.210
invested
in a diverse portfolio

06:34.210 --> 06:36.380
for my mom's foundation
to handle all the payouts.

06:36.380 --> 06:38.500
Oh, you have ping-pong.
[ Laughs ]

06:38.500 --> 06:39.830
[ Elevator bell dings ]

06:39.830 --> 06:41.120
So, you got the whole place
to yourself, huh?

06:41.120 --> 06:43.120
Yes. No sisters, no kids.

06:43.120 --> 06:45.330
First time
in recent memory.

06:45.330 --> 06:47.330
Do we have to go
to this party?

06:47.330 --> 06:49.880
[ Muffled
indistinct conversations ]

06:49.880 --> 06:51.210
Yes.

06:51.210 --> 06:53.880
But we don't
have to stay long.

06:53.880 --> 06:55.080
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

06:55.080 --> 06:57.210
[ Conversations continue ]

07:00.120 --> 07:01.790
Okay, good to go.
Okay.

07:01.790 --> 07:03.380
[ Doorbell chimes ]

07:03.380 --> 07:06.710
There is an MRI pending
for Mr. Evans in ICU 4.

07:06.710 --> 07:08.710
And can you check all the labs
for the 11:00 p.m. draw

07:08.710 --> 07:10.120
and get back to me if there's
anything I should know?

07:11.500 --> 07:13.460
Mrs. Karev.

07:13.460 --> 07:14.620
It's Doctor.

07:14.620 --> 07:15.580
Wait. What?

07:15.580 --> 07:17.670
Hi. Mrs. Karev. Hi.

07:17.670 --> 07:19.120
You're in Seattle.

07:19.120 --> 07:20.710
[ Laughs ]
Jo. Hi.

07:20.710 --> 07:23.290
Surprise! [ Laughs ]
Um, is everything okay?

07:23.290 --> 07:24.790
Does Alex know
that you're here?
Oh, yeah.

07:24.790 --> 07:26.330
But he told me to
meet him at a party?

07:26.330 --> 07:30.500
Oh. Uh...okay. Um...

07:30.500 --> 07:32.920
Uh, we must have got
our wires crossed.

07:32.920 --> 07:34.170
Um...great.

07:34.170 --> 07:35.920
I-I can give you
a ride there.

07:35.920 --> 07:37.830
Wonderful.

07:37.830 --> 07:39.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:39.620 --> 07:43.500
♪♪

07:49.170 --> 07:50.920
[ Rings ]

07:50.920 --> 07:51.960
Alex: You've reached
Chief Alex Karev.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.750
Leave a message.
[ Beeps ]

07:53.750 --> 07:55.000
Hey, Alex.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.460
It's me again.

07:56.460 --> 07:57.880
And your mom.

07:57.880 --> 08:01.040
On our way to Jackson's.

08:01.040 --> 08:01.960
See you soon.
[ Exhales sharply ]

08:01.960 --> 08:04.620
[ Beeps ]

08:04.620 --> 08:06.290
Did you fly here, or --

08:06.290 --> 08:10.420
Oh, a bus and a train
and another bus.

08:10.420 --> 08:12.750
I-I thought flying might
be a little overwhelming.

08:12.750 --> 08:14.670
Yes. It can be.

08:14.670 --> 08:17.710
You know, I, uh --
I read this book recently,

08:17.710 --> 08:20.420
uh, about the Lewis and Clark
expedition.
Mm-hmm.

08:20.420 --> 08:23.080
And they encountered
so many hardships

08:23.080 --> 08:26.040
making almost the same journey
that I just did.

08:26.040 --> 08:29.250
So I thought, if they
could do that on horseback,

08:29.250 --> 08:32.830
fighting disease,
then why couldn't I?

08:32.830 --> 08:35.750
[ Chuckles ]

08:35.750 --> 08:37.330
[ Elevator bell dings ]

08:37.330 --> 08:40.460
[ Muffled
indistinct conversations ]

08:40.460 --> 08:41.580
Oh! Hey.
Oh.

08:41.580 --> 08:43.250
-Hey.
-[ Laughing ] Hey!

08:43.250 --> 08:45.000
Sorry you had to see that,
Hunt.

08:45.000 --> 08:46.250
But she's
just so damn happy.

08:46.250 --> 08:47.830
[ Laughing ] She can't
keep her hands off me.

08:47.830 --> 08:49.790
What? Why?
Oh, h-- he surprised me.

08:49.790 --> 08:51.540
Yeah, with a trip
to Palm Springs.

08:51.540 --> 08:53.750
A little fun in the sun
before baby makes three.

08:53.750 --> 08:55.460
Or, uh, four.

08:55.460 --> 08:56.620
What?
You're going on a trip?

08:56.620 --> 08:58.040
I mean, you're
seven months pregnant.

08:58.040 --> 08:59.880
Yeah, I'm aware of
how pregnant I am, Owen.
Yeah.

08:59.880 --> 09:01.750
It's perfectly safe
for me to travel.

09:01.750 --> 09:03.120
Yeah. First class.
She'll be in good hands.

09:03.120 --> 09:04.540
Mm. My hands.
Mm. Shall we?

09:04.540 --> 09:05.670
[ Grunting ]

09:05.670 --> 09:07.500
[ Laughs ]

09:07.500 --> 09:08.960
[ Doorbell chimes ]

09:08.960 --> 09:10.040
-Hey!
-[ Chuckling ] Hi!

09:10.040 --> 09:11.290
-Come on in!
-Good to see you.

09:11.290 --> 09:13.500
-Good to see you. All right.
-Hey.

09:13.500 --> 09:14.540
-Welcome, guys. Welcome.
-Thanks.

09:14.540 --> 09:16.040
-Hi.
-Wow.

09:16.040 --> 09:17.420
Come on in.

09:17.420 --> 09:20.380
All right, you guys, uh,
make yourselves at home.

09:20.380 --> 09:23.920
M'lady, let me, uh,
get you a club soda and cran.
Oh.

09:23.920 --> 09:25.620
You've had enough
vodka tonight.
[ Laughs ]

09:25.620 --> 09:27.620
Thank you.

09:27.620 --> 09:30.330
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:30.330 --> 09:32.420
Nothing for me,
thanks.

09:32.420 --> 09:33.670
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

09:33.670 --> 09:36.750
♪♪

09:36.750 --> 09:40.670
[ Laughter in distance ]

09:40.670 --> 09:42.920
[ Laughs ]

09:42.920 --> 09:44.380
Yes, and --
and brush your teeth

09:44.380 --> 09:47.460
when Tanya tells you to,
and no extra books, okay?

09:47.460 --> 09:48.920
I love you, too,
Elle-Belle.

09:48.920 --> 09:50.500
Bye.
[ Ping-pong ball clattering ]

09:50.500 --> 09:53.210
You ready for another?
Yes.

09:53.210 --> 09:54.460
-Hey.
-Hey.

09:54.460 --> 09:55.540
Who has the kids?

09:55.540 --> 09:57.250
Bailey and Zola
are at a sleepover,

09:57.250 --> 09:58.790
and Ellis
is with the babysitter.

09:58.790 --> 10:00.920
Wow, empty house?

10:00.920 --> 10:03.540
Maybe I should, uh,
go home with you.

10:03.540 --> 10:05.960
I actually wanted
to tell you --
I have no idea

10:05.960 --> 10:07.710
what is going on
with Owen and me.

10:07.710 --> 10:09.500
And why we are even sleeping
in the same bed.

10:09.500 --> 10:11.250
I mean, it's not like
we're having any sex.

10:11.250 --> 10:13.420
We went from ex-sex

10:13.420 --> 10:15.920
to bickering married couple
in, like, 60 seconds.

10:15.920 --> 10:18.330
And now -- now
Betty and Leo are gone,

10:18.330 --> 10:20.080
and we're just
both stuck in this,

10:20.080 --> 10:22.330
you know,
giant sinkhole of sadness.

10:22.330 --> 10:24.330
We've just been so focused
on the kids,

10:24.330 --> 10:26.120
we didn't take time
to assess the damage

10:26.120 --> 10:27.580
that we were doing to us.

10:27.580 --> 10:30.620
[ Sighs ]

10:30.620 --> 10:32.460
This sucks.

10:32.460 --> 10:33.830
I mean, I say, "us,"
but is there really an "us"

10:33.830 --> 10:36.120
with no sex and no family?

10:36.120 --> 10:37.420
Can I get you another glass
of wine there?

10:37.420 --> 10:40.290
[ Groans ]
Or anything but that?

10:40.290 --> 10:42.000
She's got, like,
a kajillion likes.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.460
Listen to this --
"I had to find the courage

10:44.460 --> 10:47.210
to find the answers
I could not find."

10:47.210 --> 10:49.170
It's clearly way too many
"finds" in one sentence.

10:49.170 --> 10:50.670
No, I barely get
a mention --

10:50.670 --> 10:53.330
It's all about the bravery
and humility it took

10:53.330 --> 10:57.500
to beg me to do a radical,
pioneering surgery --

10:57.500 --> 11:00.960
These egg rolls are going
like hotcakes.

11:00.960 --> 11:02.620
Oh, are you talking
about that article?

11:02.620 --> 11:04.750
Mnh-mnh.
Oh, that was something!

11:04.750 --> 11:06.830
You know, really --
really moving.

11:06.830 --> 11:08.040
You come off very well.

11:08.040 --> 11:09.960
It's like
she healed herself

11:09.960 --> 11:11.880
with the magical power
of her own narcissism.
[ Chuckles ]

11:11.880 --> 11:13.920
I need more wine.

11:13.920 --> 11:15.330
Yeah.
Babe, I just off--

11:15.330 --> 11:16.830
♪♪

11:16.830 --> 11:18.580
Have you seen my mom?

11:18.580 --> 11:22.120
[ Engine rumbling ]

11:22.120 --> 11:23.080
[ Glasses clink ]

11:23.080 --> 11:24.790
Oh.
[ Laughs ]

11:24.790 --> 11:27.120
I could get used to this.

11:27.120 --> 11:29.080
Yes, you can.

11:29.080 --> 11:30.920
What's to stop you?

11:30.920 --> 11:32.620
Hmm.
Well, you have
money now, right?

11:32.620 --> 11:34.920
[ Glasses clatter ]
With that butt-blazer?

11:34.920 --> 11:36.040
T-Trail-Blazer.

11:36.040 --> 11:37.670
It's a golden...
[ Sighs ]

11:37.670 --> 11:39.080
...butt-cork.

11:39.080 --> 11:40.540
And you should
spend some of it.

11:40.540 --> 11:41.790
No -- I have!

11:41.790 --> 11:43.620
No, I-I paid off my car,

11:43.620 --> 11:45.540
this year's
property taxes.

11:45.540 --> 11:50.040
Oh, yeah, and Ben and I did,
uh, replace the garage door.

11:50.040 --> 11:51.670
That's just taking care
of business.

11:51.670 --> 11:52.920
What have you done
for you?

11:54.250 --> 11:55.670
W--

11:55.670 --> 11:57.790
We need to talk.
[ Glass clinks, liquid pours ]

11:57.790 --> 11:58.920
Uh -- [ Sighs ]

11:58.920 --> 12:00.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:00.620 --> 12:04.620
♪♪

12:04.620 --> 12:05.790
Oh, thanks.
No, no. This one.

12:05.790 --> 12:07.290
[ Chuckles ]

12:07.290 --> 12:09.120
You hate this party,
don't you?

12:09.120 --> 12:10.790
No. No,
I-I don't hate this party.

12:10.790 --> 12:12.000
No, I feel bad.
I mean, it's great.

12:12.000 --> 12:13.420
It's -- It's in my honor,

12:13.420 --> 12:15.210
"For I'm a jolly good fellow"
and all that,

12:15.210 --> 12:18.290
but, uh, for you, it's like
a gauntlet of awkwardness.

12:18.290 --> 12:21.420
Baby-daddy is really
not happy about our trip.

12:21.420 --> 12:24.420
Yeah, not his best moment
[sighs]

12:24.420 --> 12:26.080
but, in fairness,

12:26.080 --> 12:29.960
I mean, he and Amelia had to say
goodbye to both their kids.

12:29.960 --> 12:31.750
We can go, if you want.

12:31.750 --> 12:33.880
I will feign diarrhea.
[ Doorbell chimes ]

12:33.880 --> 12:36.040
[ Laughing ] No, you won't.
No, for you,
I will get diarrhea.

12:36.040 --> 12:37.620
No, stop it. Stop it!
[ Muffled ]
I will. I will --

12:37.620 --> 12:39.380
[ Laughing ]

12:39.380 --> 12:41.120
Why?

12:41.120 --> 12:42.500
[ Sighs ]

12:42.500 --> 12:45.000
-Oh. Hey.
-Hey.

12:45.000 --> 12:45.920
Have you seen my mom?

12:45.920 --> 12:47.210
Not your mom.

12:47.210 --> 12:48.580
Uh, i-is Alex here?

12:48.580 --> 12:49.830
Do you mind grabbing him
for me?

12:49.830 --> 12:51.250
Can I grab...

12:52.500 --> 12:54.040
Um, yeah.
Yeah, sure.

12:54.040 --> 12:55.420
-Okay.
-Yeah.

12:55.420 --> 12:57.380
Um, I'm going to update
an intern

12:57.380 --> 12:59.210
on a patient
just real quick.

12:59.210 --> 13:01.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:01.040 --> 13:04.580
♪♪

13:04.580 --> 13:06.500
Mom?

13:06.500 --> 13:08.000
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:08.000 --> 13:09.500
[ Laughter in distance ]

13:09.500 --> 13:10.620
[ Sighs ]

13:10.620 --> 13:12.580
What's wrong?
Hey, Jo, what's wrong?

13:12.580 --> 13:14.040
Nothing's wrong.

13:14.040 --> 13:15.580
W-- You didn't tell her
to meet you here?

13:15.580 --> 13:17.210
Uh, no.

13:17.210 --> 13:19.040
No, it was --
It was the other doctor.

13:19.040 --> 13:21.380
Not Alex.
Uh, wait, w-what doctor?

13:21.380 --> 13:23.250
What -- What doctor are you
talking -- Jo, what's she --

13:23.250 --> 13:24.460
I don't know.

13:24.460 --> 13:26.580
She didn't give me her name.
All right.

13:26.580 --> 13:30.670
Mom, could you, um, could you
give us a sec, please?

13:30.670 --> 13:31.920
[ Footsteps ]

13:31.920 --> 13:33.380
She was in the lobby.

13:33.380 --> 13:34.920
Of the hospital?
Yeah, to surprise you.

13:34.920 --> 13:36.120
You didn't say for her
to meet you here?

13:36.120 --> 13:37.880
No.
[ Gasps ]

13:37.880 --> 13:39.830
[ Hushed ] Do you think the
other doctor's in her head?

13:39.830 --> 13:41.880
-Why didn't you call me?
-You didn't pick up your phone!

13:41.880 --> 13:42.960
I was playing ping-pong.

13:42.960 --> 13:44.040
Catherine's party
has ping-pong?

13:44.040 --> 13:45.620
[ Elevator bell dings ]
[ Exhales sharply ]
How did she seem?

13:45.620 --> 13:46.960
Did she seem hyper?
[ Sighs ]

13:46.960 --> 13:48.460
Um, you know,
seeing things?

13:48.460 --> 13:50.960
She was, um -- She was
talking a lot for her.

13:50.960 --> 13:51.790
Or, at least, I think.
I...

13:51.790 --> 13:53.080
About what?

13:53.080 --> 13:55.290
Lewis and Clark.

13:55.290 --> 13:56.500
Huh?

13:57.960 --> 13:59.540
All right. Look, um...

13:59.540 --> 14:01.120
I'm -- I'm just gonna get her
back to our place, all right?

14:01.120 --> 14:02.290
Perfect.

14:02.290 --> 14:04.540
♪♪

14:04.540 --> 14:06.670
Uh, Mom?
No.

14:06.670 --> 14:07.500
-Mom?
-No!

14:13.170 --> 14:14.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:14.420 --> 14:15.750
Alex: Hey. Hey!

14:15.750 --> 14:17.460
How many ways are there
out of here?

14:17.460 --> 14:19.170
Why?
Look, just -- Are --
Is there, like,

14:19.170 --> 14:20.830
panic rooms or any place
somewhere someone could hide?

14:20.830 --> 14:22.920
[ Scoffs ] Very funny, Karev.
The place is not that big.

14:22.920 --> 14:24.330
Just tell me!

14:24.330 --> 14:26.420
Front door.
Or the fire exit upstairs.

14:26.420 --> 14:27.670
Right. All right.

14:27.670 --> 14:29.620
I don't have
a panic room!

14:29.620 --> 14:32.330
Not smart
to announce that.

14:32.330 --> 14:33.920
Mom?

14:33.920 --> 14:35.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:35.420 --> 14:38.170
[ Ping-pong ball clacking ]

14:38.170 --> 14:41.500
♪♪

14:41.500 --> 14:43.830
Hey.

14:43.830 --> 14:46.120
We're at a party.

14:46.120 --> 14:47.710
Yep.

14:47.710 --> 14:51.120
And you're standing out here
by yourself on the deck.

14:51.120 --> 14:52.420
You okay?

14:52.420 --> 14:54.120
[ Breathes deeply ]

14:54.120 --> 14:55.920
That looks really good
right now.

14:57.580 --> 14:59.880
You want to leave?
Uh, go to a meeting? Or --

14:59.880 --> 15:00.920
No, I'm saying --

15:00.920 --> 15:02.250
Should I not
be drinking, or --

15:02.250 --> 15:03.920
No, t-t-that's not --

15:03.920 --> 15:06.170
I mean, I'm at a party --
Owen, that is not
what I'm saying.

15:06.170 --> 15:09.040
I'm -- I'm saying
I'm sad, too.

15:09.040 --> 15:10.880
I'm saying sometimes I wish

15:10.880 --> 15:12.540
I could drink
like a normal person.

15:12.540 --> 15:14.790
And -- It's not a big deal.
Just finish your stupid drink.

15:14.790 --> 15:17.250
[ Clacking continues ]

15:17.250 --> 15:19.250
Did I do something to you?

15:19.250 --> 15:21.830
Are we fighting
and I missed it?

15:21.830 --> 15:23.830
Is that a yes?

15:23.830 --> 15:25.290
Really?

15:25.290 --> 15:26.830
We're fighting?

15:26.830 --> 15:28.250
That's what you want to do

15:28.250 --> 15:30.580
the night that we said goodbye
to Betty and Leo?

15:31.580 --> 15:33.290
She didn't say goodbye.

15:33.290 --> 15:35.960
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:35.960 --> 15:39.250
♪♪

15:39.250 --> 15:40.670
Look, I don't want to fight.
I just want to talk.

15:40.670 --> 15:43.540
We have not talked
in weeks.

15:43.540 --> 15:45.500
Okay, let's talk.

15:45.500 --> 15:46.920
Okay.

15:47.670 --> 15:50.290
Let's talk.

15:50.290 --> 15:51.960
Where do we start?

15:51.960 --> 15:54.580
How about "piss poor
life choices"?
Wow.

15:54.580 --> 15:58.420
Or how you refuse to accept
that addiction is a disease?

15:58.420 --> 16:00.000
I never said that.
You may as well have.

16:00.000 --> 16:01.710
Why do you do that?

16:01.710 --> 16:04.000
You always throw things in
my face that I said months ago.

16:04.000 --> 16:06.420
I hate it.
And I hate -- I hate

16:06.420 --> 16:10.540
that you have not asked me how
I have been through any of this.

16:10.540 --> 16:13.080
I've be in pain, Amelia.
Yeah, and when you're
in pain, you go silent.

16:13.080 --> 16:14.750
You -- You keep it
all inside.

16:14.750 --> 16:16.750
You act like you are all alone
in it, and you are not.

16:16.750 --> 16:18.960
Yeah, because I-I-I-I
haven't been able to fix it.

16:18.960 --> 16:20.750
So I just --
So -- So we should
just never talk about it?

16:20.750 --> 16:22.040
We don't never talk
about it.

16:22.040 --> 16:24.540
I hate [inhales deeply]
how you generalize.

16:24.540 --> 16:26.420
You know, "You always do this,
and you always do that."

16:26.420 --> 16:28.710
Okay, you literally
just did that to me.

16:28.710 --> 16:31.420
You said I "always"
throw things in your face.

16:31.420 --> 16:33.830
[ Scoffs ]

16:33.830 --> 16:35.920
Are we trying to talk,
or are you just trying to win?

16:35.920 --> 16:38.620
Well, I wanted to talk,
but it's kind of hard

16:38.620 --> 16:41.580
when you have been staring
at Teddy the entire time.

16:41.580 --> 16:43.790
-How about you?
-[ Laughs ]

16:43.790 --> 16:45.500
[ Laughter in distance ]

16:45.500 --> 16:48.380
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

16:53.540 --> 16:54.750
Thank you.

16:54.750 --> 16:57.250
Hey!
Hey.

16:57.250 --> 17:00.250
Mm. Nice article.

17:00.250 --> 17:03.250
Really? Teddy? Was it?
[ Cork pops ]

17:03.250 --> 17:05.460
Or was it just some puff piece
on a website

17:05.460 --> 17:07.620
that may as well
be called "OMG! BOYS!"

17:07.620 --> 17:09.330
Well, I mean, I thought
it was really --
No.

17:09.330 --> 17:10.580
You know, they should
really read my piece

17:10.580 --> 17:11.880
that I just submitted

17:11.880 --> 17:13.250
to the Journal
of Cardiothoracic Advancement,

17:13.250 --> 17:15.880
where I actually outline
the procedure!

17:15.880 --> 17:18.380
All right, well,
I'll do that when --
No, you won't.

17:18.380 --> 17:19.960
Because they probably
won't even publish it now,

17:19.960 --> 17:22.960
because it's just
the same story, only boring.

17:22.960 --> 17:24.000
'Cause who needs science

17:24.000 --> 17:26.250
when there's pluckiness
and spunk?

17:26.250 --> 17:29.960
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:29.960 --> 17:33.620
[ Panting ]

17:33.620 --> 17:34.960
Helen?

17:34.960 --> 17:37.420
[ Conversations continue ]

17:37.420 --> 17:40.920
♪♪

17:40.920 --> 17:42.920
I do hate this party.

17:42.920 --> 17:45.210
♪♪

17:45.210 --> 17:47.250
Hey. You're leaving?

17:47.250 --> 17:48.960
Hi. I, um...

17:48.960 --> 17:51.120
Tanya called, and Ellis
is really scared, so...

17:51.120 --> 17:52.670
Oh, oh,
I can pick her up.

17:52.670 --> 17:54.250
No. It's a party
in your honor.

17:54.250 --> 17:56.420
You can't leave.
It's not really an honor

17:56.420 --> 17:58.750
when you didn't
get 100% margins.

17:58.750 --> 18:02.290
And on top of that, I think Owen
still has feelings for Teddy.

18:02.290 --> 18:04.040
You should have seen
how he reacted

18:04.040 --> 18:06.000
when he found out that she was
going on vacation with Koracick.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.420
Teddy is always going
to be in Owen's life.

18:08.420 --> 18:10.000
Baby or no baby.

18:10.000 --> 18:11.620
It was this way
for Cristina.

18:11.620 --> 18:13.670
It's been this way
your whole marriage.

18:13.670 --> 18:16.000
And your divorce.

18:16.000 --> 18:17.580
It's not gonna change.

18:17.580 --> 18:20.000
Just make peace with it.

18:20.000 --> 18:21.540
[ Inhales sharply ]

18:21.540 --> 18:23.420
I'm not in a love triangle.
This is a circle.

18:23.420 --> 18:25.540
And it just keeps going
around and around.

18:27.540 --> 18:30.170
I'm definitely staying
at your place tonight.

18:32.790 --> 18:35.670
[ Sighs ]

18:35.670 --> 18:37.830
Historians believe
that Meriwether Lewis

18:37.830 --> 18:39.750
had bipolar disorder,

18:39.750 --> 18:41.540
but in
the early 19th century,

18:41.540 --> 18:44.120
they called it,
um, "melancholy."

18:44.120 --> 18:46.420
Mm. So you're
a psychologist?

18:46.420 --> 18:48.000
Librarian.
Oh.

18:48.000 --> 18:49.250
H-How do you
know Catherine?

18:49.250 --> 18:51.290
-Who?
-[ Exhales sharply ] Mom.

18:51.290 --> 18:52.500
What?

18:52.500 --> 18:54.210
[ Panting ]
Look, uh, DeLuca, thanks.

18:54.210 --> 18:55.250
Yeah.

18:55.250 --> 18:56.540
He's very nice.

18:56.540 --> 18:58.580
Yeah.
Oh, thank God.

18:58.580 --> 19:00.380
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:00.380 --> 19:01.790
Oh, I worried you.

19:01.790 --> 19:03.120
Yeah, you had us worried.

19:03.120 --> 19:04.500
I am doing well.

19:04.500 --> 19:05.880
I feel sturdy.

19:05.880 --> 19:08.040
How about I give you
both a minute?

19:08.040 --> 19:11.920
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

19:11.920 --> 19:13.460
I made something for you.

19:13.460 --> 19:15.000
Oh.

19:15.000 --> 19:18.460
When you were a little boy,
green was your favorite color,

19:18.460 --> 19:21.080
but it could have changed by
now, so you can just pick.

19:22.920 --> 19:25.380
Yeah, it's, uh -- it's not
much of a wedding gift.

19:25.380 --> 19:26.960
Uh, y-you don't
have to take one.

19:26.960 --> 19:28.830
That's okay.
No, no, no.
Green is good.

19:28.830 --> 19:29.960
It's -- It's -- It's great.

19:29.960 --> 19:32.210
It's...It's lovely.

19:32.210 --> 19:33.290
Okay, what about Jo?

19:34.580 --> 19:36.290
Blue.

19:36.290 --> 19:37.880
Okay.

19:37.880 --> 19:39.210
DeLuca: Oh, Dr. Grey.

19:39.210 --> 19:41.080
Excuse me, Bokhee, Jae.

19:42.500 --> 19:45.170
[ Speaking Korean ]

19:47.420 --> 19:48.540
Bokhee.

19:48.540 --> 19:50.080
[ Chuckles ]

19:50.080 --> 19:52.080
Uh, I got your text.
Yeah.

19:52.080 --> 19:54.670
Is everything okay?
No. Amelia's in a state.

19:54.670 --> 19:55.670
Oh.

19:55.670 --> 19:58.620
So I think
I'm on duty tonight.

19:58.620 --> 20:00.210
[ Smacks lips, sighs ]

20:00.210 --> 20:01.750
[ Muffled
indistinct conversations ]

20:01.750 --> 20:05.960
♪♪

20:05.960 --> 20:08.540
♪♪

20:08.540 --> 20:11.710
[ Breathing heavily ]

20:11.710 --> 20:16.000
[ Fire crackles ]

20:16.000 --> 20:18.210
In the guest room?
[ Laughs ]

20:19.750 --> 20:21.670
Hey.

20:21.670 --> 20:24.080
What?

20:24.080 --> 20:26.420
I'm just trying to burn this
image in my head forever.

20:28.380 --> 20:30.790
Okay, but you do realize
nothing is happening

20:30.790 --> 20:33.500
in the guest room of
Jackson Avery's house, right,

20:33.500 --> 20:35.880
with all of our co-workers
downstairs?

20:38.670 --> 20:40.000
Okay.

20:41.920 --> 20:44.380
[ Speaking Italian ]

20:46.790 --> 20:48.830
[ Muffled
indistinct conversations ]

20:52.750 --> 20:54.210
I -- Look,
I don't know how long

20:54.210 --> 20:56.290
the Trail-Blazer's success
will run.

20:56.290 --> 20:58.250
It's like, what if
somebody else comes along

20:58.250 --> 20:59.580
with something better?
[ Scoffs ]

20:59.580 --> 21:01.380
All my checks...poof.
[ Snaps fingers ]

21:01.380 --> 21:03.960
Bailey,
that's how money works.

21:03.960 --> 21:06.210
I mean, my grandfather
made a fortune

21:06.210 --> 21:08.960
when he opened
a candy store in 1921.

21:08.960 --> 21:12.540
And what happened
in 1927? Mnh.
Poof?

21:12.540 --> 21:15.210
My father didn't have shoes
that fit for over a month.

21:15.210 --> 21:17.120
Oh.
I'm just trying
to tell you

21:17.120 --> 21:19.670
that money comes,
money goes.

21:19.670 --> 21:21.500
And what's the point
if you lose it

21:21.500 --> 21:23.120
before you get to
enjoy it a little?

21:24.710 --> 21:27.830
So, you want me to buy
myself a few hospitals?

21:27.830 --> 21:29.210
How many to start, three?

21:29.210 --> 21:31.750
Start slow, honey. Okay.

21:31.750 --> 21:34.920
What is the one thing that
you haven't let yourself get?

21:34.920 --> 21:36.330
Come on. There's
got to be something.

21:37.920 --> 21:41.750
The C7500 TurboMix in red.

21:41.750 --> 21:43.880
[ Exhales sharply ]

21:43.880 --> 21:48.120
Uh, soups, smoothies, dips,
dressings, desserts --

21:48.120 --> 21:50.000
You can make
Christmas dinner with it.

21:50.000 --> 21:52.420
And...it cleans itself.

21:52.420 --> 21:53.790
Act of God.

21:53.790 --> 21:55.380
What is it?

21:55.380 --> 21:56.880
A blender.

21:56.880 --> 21:58.500
Oh, Lord. [ Scoffs ]

21:58.500 --> 22:00.290
What?
Well, you should just
buy the damn thing.

22:00.290 --> 22:01.670
[ Scoffs ]
Look at that price.

22:01.670 --> 22:04.460
Bailey, think about when
you walk into your kitchen,

22:04.460 --> 22:06.330
and it's gleaming at you
from the counter

22:06.330 --> 22:09.380
with its five
programmable speeds.

22:09.380 --> 22:11.580
The price is nothing
compared to that joy --

22:11.580 --> 22:13.880
I bought it!
[ Laughs ]

22:13.880 --> 22:15.670
[ Laughs ]
All right!

22:15.670 --> 22:17.250
[ Glass clatters ]
We got something
to celebrate.

22:17.250 --> 22:20.040
Come on.
N-No, it's almost 8:00.

22:20.040 --> 22:21.120
We need to get to the party.

22:21.120 --> 22:22.920
Oh, please,
I'm not going to that.

22:22.920 --> 22:24.380
[ Container clatters ]

22:24.380 --> 22:25.710
Mmm. [ Smacks lips ]

22:32.380 --> 22:36.750
Well, this is the last
of the duck sauce.

22:36.750 --> 22:39.420
Avery, thanks for everything,
but I gotta -- I'm heading out.

22:39.420 --> 22:40.710
What? No, no, no.
Come on.

22:40.710 --> 22:42.960
Listen, I'm sorry.
I just...

22:42.960 --> 22:44.670
God, I hate that guy.

22:44.670 --> 22:45.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:45.830 --> 22:48.670
Who -- Koracick?

22:48.670 --> 22:50.460
Oh, well, yeah.
He's a creep.

22:50.460 --> 22:52.500
What?
You think so, too?
I know so.

22:52.500 --> 22:54.830
He took advantage of April
during a pretty vulnerable time.

22:54.830 --> 22:56.460
You're kidding.
He's been after Catherine

22:56.460 --> 22:57.920
since the minute
he got into town.

22:57.920 --> 23:00.210
What is she --
What is she doing with him?

23:00.210 --> 23:02.000
I can't say I'd be thrilled
if I were you.

23:02.000 --> 23:03.330
[ Scoffs ]

23:03.330 --> 23:05.710
On the other hand,
he did save my mom's life,

23:05.710 --> 23:07.120
so I don't know.

23:07.120 --> 23:08.210
♪♪

23:08.210 --> 23:09.960
But it's a party for you!

23:09.960 --> 23:11.960
It's for Shepherd
and Koracick.

23:11.960 --> 23:13.960
Because they saved
your life.

23:13.960 --> 23:15.710
They did.

23:15.710 --> 23:17.920
They performed
an astonishing feat,

23:17.920 --> 23:19.750
and for that,
I am forever grateful.

23:19.750 --> 23:23.500
But [sighs] Miranda, if I walk
into that party right now,

23:23.500 --> 23:25.040
people are gonna come up to me
and say things like,

23:25.040 --> 23:27.170
"Oh, congratulations,"

23:27.170 --> 23:29.460
"You did it" --

23:29.460 --> 23:31.830
like it's all over,
like I'm cancer-free.

23:33.460 --> 23:36.960
Yes, my tumor hasn't gotten
any bigger, but it could.

23:36.960 --> 23:38.710
[ Sighs ]
It could.

23:38.710 --> 23:43.290
And so I have to live in dread
from one scan to the next.

23:43.290 --> 23:45.620
For every scan.

23:45.620 --> 23:48.710
I'm never gonna be out of
the woods with this thing,

23:48.710 --> 23:52.080
and it's not something
I feel like celebrating.

23:53.620 --> 23:56.000
Hypocrite.

23:56.000 --> 23:57.580
Excuse me?

23:57.580 --> 24:00.120
You're all easy come, easy go
when it comes to money,

24:00.120 --> 24:02.620
but you're afraid
to spend joy.

24:02.620 --> 24:05.250
What -- you think
you're gonna run out of it?

24:05.250 --> 24:09.120
That dread between scans
is scary.

24:09.120 --> 24:11.580
But it's life.

24:11.580 --> 24:15.920
And it's not perfect,
but it's the one you get now.

24:15.920 --> 24:17.620
W-What I get.

24:17.620 --> 24:20.710
I-I have a heart that
I no longer trust.

24:20.710 --> 24:25.670
I live day by day trying to
get it to not blow up again

24:25.670 --> 24:28.540
and hoping that the fix
they gave me stays a fix.

24:28.540 --> 24:29.750
And you?

24:29.750 --> 24:32.120
You have a piece of tumor
on your spine,

24:32.120 --> 24:36.250
and it could get bigger
or it could not.

24:36.250 --> 24:38.540
And you know what?

24:38.540 --> 24:41.750
An earthquake could take us
all out tomorrow.

24:41.750 --> 24:44.380
Or a meteor. Or robots.

24:44.380 --> 24:47.170
We don't get to know that.

24:47.170 --> 24:48.750
[ Banners' "Got It In You
(Acoustic)" plays ]

24:48.750 --> 24:52.830
But just right now,
we're alive --

24:52.830 --> 24:54.960
we are still here.

24:54.960 --> 25:00.460
And people love us,
so that's cause to celebrate.

25:00.460 --> 25:03.290
♪ Holding back the flood
in this skyscraper town ♪

25:03.290 --> 25:04.710
Hey, excuse me.

25:04.710 --> 25:06.380
Can we talk?

25:06.380 --> 25:07.920
What else is there
to talk about?

25:07.920 --> 25:09.040
Listen, I wasn't
looking at Teddy.

25:09.040 --> 25:10.960
I was looking at Koracick.

25:10.960 --> 25:12.120
Okay?
I don't like that guy.

25:12.120 --> 25:13.500
I don't like that
he's dating Teddy.

25:13.500 --> 25:14.710
Because you're jealous.

25:14.710 --> 25:17.710
No, because he's like a dog
marking his territory.

25:17.710 --> 25:20.420
And because who hits on a woman
who's seven months pregnant?

25:20.420 --> 25:22.670
That's Tom.
He's available. Always.

25:22.670 --> 25:24.710
He was available for me
after the tumor.

25:24.710 --> 25:27.040
Wait. What?
Why does it matter?

25:27.040 --> 25:29.830
If you're not interested
in Teddy, what does it matter?

25:29.830 --> 25:32.040
If he's with her, then he's
gonna be in my daughter's life,

25:32.040 --> 25:34.540
and I don't want that.

25:34.540 --> 25:36.960
This has got nothing
to do with Teddy.

25:36.960 --> 25:38.790
How many times do I have
to choose you, Amelia,

25:38.790 --> 25:40.210
for you to stop feeling
insecure?

25:40.210 --> 25:42.330
Insecure?

25:42.330 --> 25:44.290
This is not about some fling
from your past.

25:44.290 --> 25:46.540
She is pregnant
with your child right now

25:46.540 --> 25:49.790
because you got on a plane
to profess your love to her

25:49.790 --> 25:51.040
seven months ago.

25:51.040 --> 25:53.380
Not -- Not seven years.
Seven months.

25:53.380 --> 25:55.580
So forgive me for worrying
that maybe your feelings

25:55.580 --> 25:57.170
might still be lingering,

25:57.170 --> 25:59.540
and that maybe
when you see your baby,

25:59.540 --> 26:02.170
you are gonna realize how deeply
you are in love with her.

26:02.170 --> 26:05.920
You and I fell back in love
over children that we adored

26:05.920 --> 26:08.290
and that
we no longer have.

26:08.290 --> 26:09.540
Okay? Do you
really think that,

26:09.540 --> 26:11.000
when you see your daughter
lying in Teddy's arms,

26:11.000 --> 26:12.540
that you are not gonna think

26:12.540 --> 26:13.960
that maybe this is
where you belong?

26:13.960 --> 26:15.580
Because I do.

26:15.580 --> 26:17.040
And maybe you're right.
Maybe that is insecurity.

26:17.040 --> 26:19.250
Or maybe it is wisdom.

26:19.250 --> 26:21.330
Whatever you want to call it,
it is what I believe.

26:21.330 --> 26:22.620
And I cannot talk my way
out of it.

26:22.620 --> 26:24.290
I can't.

26:24.290 --> 26:26.500
And I'm starting
to think maybe I...

26:26.500 --> 26:28.290
♪ Maybe you don't see it ♪

26:28.290 --> 26:30.790
I'm starting to think
I shouldn't try.

26:30.790 --> 26:32.830
♪ But you're quicker
than the world can spin ♪

26:32.830 --> 26:35.960
What are you saying?
I'm saying I'm dizzy.

26:35.960 --> 26:39.000
Owen, I'm -- [ Sighs ]
I'm dizzy.

26:39.000 --> 26:40.710
I need to step out
of the circle.

26:40.710 --> 26:42.920
What?

26:42.920 --> 26:44.670
I'm saying this
is an impossible situation.

26:44.670 --> 26:47.580
And you are in it
no matter what

26:47.580 --> 26:48.830
because there is a child
involved.

26:48.830 --> 26:50.170
But I'm not.
I'm not in it, no matter what.

26:50.170 --> 26:51.420
I'm saying...

26:51.420 --> 26:53.250
♪♪

26:53.250 --> 26:54.250
♪ When the lights go out ♪

26:54.250 --> 26:56.250
I'm saying I'm not in it
anymore.

26:56.250 --> 26:58.750
♪ And leave you standing
in the dark ♪

26:58.750 --> 27:00.540
[ Breathes sharply ]

27:00.540 --> 27:03.460
♪ No one ever told you
this would be so hard ♪

27:03.460 --> 27:05.420
Hey, uh, Dr. Lummis,
this is Alex Karev,

27:05.420 --> 27:07.000
uh, Helen Karev's son.

27:07.000 --> 27:08.580
If you could, uh,
give me a call back

27:08.580 --> 27:10.120
as soon as you can --
it's pretty urgent.

27:10.120 --> 27:11.210
Please.

27:11.210 --> 27:12.580
They're two hours ahead.

27:12.580 --> 27:14.920
Y-You're not gonna hear
from them until tomorrow.

27:14.920 --> 27:17.330
Right. I should
probably text, too.

27:17.330 --> 27:19.000
Hey. Here. Come here.
Come sit down.

27:19.000 --> 27:20.040
Come here.

27:20.040 --> 27:21.540
♪ You got it in you ♪

27:21.540 --> 27:22.620
[ Sighs ]

27:22.620 --> 27:24.080
♪ When the lights go out ♪

27:24.080 --> 27:25.380
She seems okay.

27:25.380 --> 27:26.500
♪ And leave you standing
in the dark ♪

27:26.500 --> 27:27.790
The doctor will call.

27:27.790 --> 27:30.580
And then we will find out
what's going on.

27:30.580 --> 27:32.960
My mom comes for a visit,
and I have to worry

27:32.960 --> 27:35.880
if it's a sign she's gonna
split from reality.

27:35.880 --> 27:37.170
Isn't that how
it's always been?

27:37.170 --> 27:38.790
Well, yeah.
Growing up.

27:38.790 --> 27:40.790
But then, you could tell
when things were getting bad.

27:40.790 --> 27:42.210
I knew the signs.

27:42.210 --> 27:43.500
I mean, now that
she's doing fine,

27:43.500 --> 27:45.880
I d-- I don't know
what a split looks like.

27:45.880 --> 27:47.960
[ Sighs ]
I want to trust it.

27:47.960 --> 27:49.710
I want to trust it so much
that she's fine.

27:49.710 --> 27:52.830
I really do.
I swear, Jo.
I know.

27:52.830 --> 27:55.500
These are really nice.

27:55.500 --> 27:57.250
She shouldn't have needles.

27:57.250 --> 27:59.330
[ Vocalizing ]

27:59.330 --> 28:02.120
♪♪

28:02.120 --> 28:04.250
♪ You got it in you ♪

28:04.250 --> 28:06.000
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:06.000 --> 28:07.790
[ Fire crackling ]

28:11.960 --> 28:13.830
♪♪

28:13.830 --> 28:16.460
Okay, we --
we should stop now.

28:16.460 --> 28:17.710
Why?

28:17.710 --> 28:19.620
Because I'm going to
change my mind.

28:19.620 --> 28:21.080
Sounds good.

28:21.080 --> 28:23.460
♪♪

28:23.460 --> 28:24.710
[ Cellphone rings ]

28:24.710 --> 28:26.080
Ohh.
[ Sighs ]

28:26.080 --> 28:27.960
Just answer it.

28:27.960 --> 28:29.210
I don't care who it is.

28:29.210 --> 28:31.380
[ Ringing continues ]

28:31.380 --> 28:33.710
But someone might
hear it ringing.

28:33.710 --> 28:35.000
[ Sighs ]

28:35.000 --> 28:35.920
[ Ringing continues ]

28:35.920 --> 28:38.210
[ Sighs ] It's Carina.

28:38.210 --> 28:39.790
[ Cellphone beeps,
ringing stops ]

28:39.790 --> 28:42.330
Oh. Our sisters are really
getting in the way tonight.

28:42.330 --> 28:43.580
Yeah, they really are.

28:43.580 --> 28:44.670
[ Both laugh ]

28:46.670 --> 28:48.540
Oh. Uh...

28:48.540 --> 28:49.330
Um...

28:51.500 --> 28:53.710
This is
not the restroom.

28:53.710 --> 28:55.670
No, that's, uh --
that's down the hall.

28:55.670 --> 28:57.330
♪♪

28:57.330 --> 28:58.960
We're not...

28:58.960 --> 29:00.250
I...

29:02.460 --> 29:04.210
[ Sighs ] Alex knows.

29:05.380 --> 29:06.380
W-Wonderful.

29:06.380 --> 29:09.500
Uh, don't let me keep you.

29:09.500 --> 29:11.170
Hmm.

29:13.170 --> 29:14.960
[ Softly ] Oh, my --
[ Laughs ]

29:14.960 --> 29:16.830
I told you!

29:16.830 --> 29:18.460
It's not funny!
It's not funny!

29:18.460 --> 29:19.500
[ Both laughing ]

29:25.170 --> 29:27.960
Hey. I can do this.
Thanks.

29:27.960 --> 29:30.960
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:30.960 --> 29:32.540
What are you doing?

29:32.540 --> 29:34.170
Oh, I'm being normal.

29:34.170 --> 29:36.380
Huh.
Will you put these
in the oven for me?

29:36.380 --> 29:37.670
I don't think
this counts as normal.

29:37.670 --> 29:39.330
Jackson hired people
to do this.

29:39.330 --> 29:41.250
Just do it.
Okay, you're flustered.

29:41.250 --> 29:43.120
Yes,
I'm getting flustered.

29:43.120 --> 29:44.420
Richard just
walked in on us.

29:44.420 --> 29:46.830
Yeah, kissing.

29:46.830 --> 29:48.040
At a work party.

29:48.040 --> 29:50.380
So now I feel like
everybody's staring at us.

29:50.380 --> 29:51.960
No one is staring at us.

29:53.000 --> 29:54.710
Because we're
acting normal.

29:54.710 --> 29:57.500
♪♪

29:57.500 --> 30:01.000
And after going to many doctors,
this woman found Maggie.

30:01.000 --> 30:03.040
She was
a med school acquaintance,

30:03.040 --> 30:04.120
and after that,
they --

30:04.120 --> 30:06.170
Excuse us.
Just one second.

30:06.170 --> 30:07.380
-[ Laughs ]
-Uh, excuse me for a second.

30:07.380 --> 30:08.710
[ Hushed voice ]
Please stop telling people

30:08.710 --> 30:11.460
about that article,
please?
Why? It's very nice.

30:11.460 --> 30:14.250
No, it's not.
And she is not.

30:14.250 --> 30:17.380
That was my story to tell,
for doctors,

30:17.380 --> 30:20.120
in a way that mattered,
and she stole it.

30:20.120 --> 30:23.710
She is a bully who made me
feel small and insignificant,

30:23.710 --> 30:26.250
and she is still managing,
even from a thousand miles away,

30:26.250 --> 30:27.750
to make me feel small
and insignificant!

30:27.750 --> 30:28.960
Maggie Pierce.
You are not small and insig--
No, no!

30:28.960 --> 30:30.500
Please, please, don't --

30:30.500 --> 30:33.250
don't say anything kind
or comforting or consoling.

30:33.250 --> 30:35.120
I'm pissed.
I want to stay pissed.

30:35.120 --> 30:37.250
I want
to burn something down!

30:37.250 --> 30:38.830
[ Groans ]

30:38.830 --> 30:43.710
♪♪

30:43.710 --> 30:47.880
Did you know that I was the only
black resident in my class?

30:47.880 --> 30:49.710
So I was bullied, too.

30:49.710 --> 30:52.620
Residents would take my number
off the pager service...

30:52.620 --> 30:56.290
[ Whispering ] Oh, my God.
...so I'd miss traumas.

30:56.290 --> 30:59.290
Some of the attendings would
call the other residents "Dr."

30:59.290 --> 31:02.000
But I only got "Webber."

31:02.000 --> 31:04.460
And I was plenty pissed.

31:06.250 --> 31:09.790
But I found out that
it's no good to be pissed

31:09.790 --> 31:12.170
if you don't use it.

31:12.170 --> 31:14.040
You know, the difference
between a great surgeon

31:14.040 --> 31:15.960
and a celebration
surgeon...

31:15.960 --> 31:18.290
is a little bit
of what Kiki has.

31:18.290 --> 31:20.210
A little flair
for promotion.

31:20.210 --> 31:21.580
You could use
a little of that.

31:21.580 --> 31:24.250
If someone takes your story,
you take it back,

31:24.250 --> 31:26.960
and you tell it louder.

31:26.960 --> 31:29.960
Stop publication of that piece,
and rewrite it,

31:29.960 --> 31:32.120
from your point of view.

31:32.120 --> 31:34.830
Start that fire,
Maggie Pierce.

31:34.830 --> 31:37.040
[ Laughter in distance ]

31:37.040 --> 31:40.330
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

31:40.330 --> 31:43.580
[ Fire crackling ]

31:43.580 --> 31:45.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:45.420 --> 31:50.830
♪♪

31:50.830 --> 31:52.750
Hi. You want something
to eat?

31:52.750 --> 31:54.290
[ Sighs ]
I'm happy to see you.

31:54.290 --> 31:57.080
It's just, uh,
it threw me.

31:57.080 --> 31:58.960
I mean, uh --

31:58.960 --> 32:01.330
I mean, it really means a lot
for Jo and me both.

32:02.500 --> 32:04.790
Tires. No.

32:04.790 --> 32:07.210
Tennis shoes.

32:07.210 --> 32:08.960
Melting tennis shoes.
What?

32:08.960 --> 32:11.710
Don't you smell that?
No.

32:11.710 --> 32:14.000
All right, t-take it easy.
Take it easy.

32:14.000 --> 32:15.670
[ Stammers ]
The -- The shoes --

32:15.670 --> 32:17.120
The shoes you had in
high school, the red ones.

32:17.120 --> 32:18.250
Remember?
They were on sale.

32:18.250 --> 32:20.620
But they're
[stammers] burning.

32:20.620 --> 32:22.670
The shoe--

32:22.670 --> 32:24.960
Alex,
we are really high up.

32:24.960 --> 32:26.170
Honestly, everybody needs
to get out of here right now.

32:26.170 --> 32:27.620
But, Mom,
there is no fire.

32:27.620 --> 32:30.420
Yes, there is!
There is!

32:30.420 --> 32:32.790
Mom, come on. Just stop.
Just calm down.

32:32.790 --> 32:35.080
Come on. Sit down.
Come on. Please?

32:35.080 --> 32:36.880
It's gonna be all right.

32:36.880 --> 32:38.880
[ Laughs ]

32:38.880 --> 32:41.330
I am a little hungry.

32:41.330 --> 32:43.880
[ Sighs ] What if you go into
labor when you're out of town?

32:43.880 --> 32:46.040
They have hospitals
in California --

32:46.040 --> 32:47.830
But I wouldn't be there.

32:47.830 --> 32:50.000
Well, a flight
is not even three hours.

32:50.000 --> 32:51.420
I wanna be there.

32:51.420 --> 32:54.210
I understand that,
but I'm taking this trip.

32:54.210 --> 32:55.880
[ Scoffs ]

32:55.880 --> 32:57.330
And what is this about,
Teddy?

32:57.330 --> 32:59.710
You want that dirtbag
in the delivery room?

32:59.710 --> 33:01.460
Whoa.
I mean, do you want him
around our daughter?

33:01.460 --> 33:03.170
He is not a good guy.

33:03.170 --> 33:05.670
I think he's a great guy.

33:05.670 --> 33:07.620
And he saved Amelia's life,
and he's --

33:07.620 --> 33:10.080
Hey.
Uh, pickles,

33:10.080 --> 33:12.000
uh, seven almonds,
pasteurized cheese.

33:12.000 --> 33:13.250
But one of the almonds
is for me.
Thank you.

33:13.250 --> 33:15.210
[ Chuckling ] Okay.
Uh, do you mind?

33:15.210 --> 33:16.460
Uh, we're in the middle
of something.

33:16.460 --> 33:18.880
I do mind.
But thanks for asking.

33:18.880 --> 33:20.710
[ Doorbell chimes ]

33:20.710 --> 33:22.250
[ Laughter ]

33:22.250 --> 33:23.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:23.420 --> 33:25.670
-Mom. Hey. You made it.
-Oh.

33:25.670 --> 33:27.500
Yeah. Mm.
Finally.

33:27.500 --> 33:29.880
[ Scoffs ]
She's your problem now.

33:29.880 --> 33:32.000
All right. Everyone!

33:32.000 --> 33:33.670
Our guest of honor is here.
[ Applause ]

33:33.670 --> 33:35.500
There's nothing fun
about any of this.
Alex, we have to
get out of here.

33:35.500 --> 33:36.500
All right,
w-we're gonna go.

33:36.500 --> 33:37.710
-We're gonna leave.
-No, uh --

33:37.710 --> 33:39.670
Karev. Can you just stay
till after the toast?

33:39.670 --> 33:41.620
Owen: Do you hear him, Teddy?
Do you hear these words...

33:41.620 --> 33:43.330
Mom, come on over.
All right, folks, over here.
Oh.

33:43.330 --> 33:44.580
Koracick:
You're starting to upset her.
And embarrass yourself.

33:44.580 --> 33:46.380
Hey.
She's seven months
pregnant, Tom,

33:46.380 --> 33:47.960
so why don't you just
do the right thing?
So, what -- what,

33:47.960 --> 33:49.750
we're on a first-name basis now?
Because I barely know you.

33:49.750 --> 33:52.040
Wait. What was it again?
It was Oliver? Ollie?
No, no, I know you.

33:52.040 --> 33:53.500
Because any man
who would prey on

33:53.500 --> 33:54.580
a vulnerable
pregnant woman --
Jackson: Okay, over here.

33:54.580 --> 33:56.000
Okay, okay,
this was a blast,

33:56.000 --> 33:57.250
but I shouldn't keep
my public waiting.

33:57.250 --> 33:58.380
And I will tell you another
thing, Tom.

33:58.380 --> 33:59.460
If you think you're gonna
be around my kid,

33:59.460 --> 34:00.580
then you have
another thing coming.

34:00.580 --> 34:01.880
'Cause you may be
many things,

34:01.880 --> 34:03.750
but a father
isn't one of them!
Owen!

34:03.750 --> 34:04.750
[ Groans ]
[ All shouting ]

34:04.750 --> 34:06.080
-Oh, wow!
-What the hell?!

34:06.080 --> 34:08.250
-Oh!
-Okay. I'm done.

34:08.250 --> 34:10.420
-Owen!
-Owen, he is a father!

34:10.420 --> 34:11.880
All right,
if you're gonna punch him,

34:11.880 --> 34:13.120
you're gonna have to go through
a pregnant woman.

34:13.120 --> 34:15.330
[ Scoffs ]

34:15.330 --> 34:17.710
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I...
-Oh, don't be. All right.

34:22.830 --> 34:27.080
Million dollar hand.
Sorry, Avery, proceed.

34:27.080 --> 34:30.580
Yeah. Um, anyway,
as you can see,

34:30.580 --> 34:32.750
I am so happy to be standing
here with --

34:32.750 --> 34:33.880
[ Gasps ] Fire!

34:33.880 --> 34:35.750
[ All murmuring ]

34:35.750 --> 34:37.620
-What's that?
-It's a fire.

34:37.620 --> 34:39.380
It's a real fire!
[ Smoke alarm beeps rapidly,
indistinct chatter ]

34:39.380 --> 34:40.790
Uh, all right,
well, okay --

34:40.790 --> 34:42.420
There appears to be
a small situation here.

34:42.420 --> 34:44.250
Just carefully -- if you all
could make your way...

34:44.250 --> 34:45.250
Be safe.

34:45.250 --> 34:46.540
-[ Screams ]
-Oh, no!

34:46.540 --> 34:47.790
[ Indistinct chatter ]

34:47.790 --> 34:49.460
Come on, everybody.
It's a real fire!

34:49.460 --> 34:51.290
Come on, Mom.

34:51.290 --> 34:52.500
[ All murmuring ]

34:57.960 --> 35:00.210
[ Sirens wailing,
indistinct shouting ]

35:00.210 --> 35:02.670
[ Horn honks ]

35:02.670 --> 35:03.920
[ Wailing fades ]

35:03.920 --> 35:05.330
[ Indistinct conversations ]

35:05.330 --> 35:07.750
I told you I didn't want
to have a party.

35:09.750 --> 35:12.250
Ben: If I could get
everyone's attention, please,

35:12.250 --> 35:14.500
the building is cleared
for re-entry.

35:14.500 --> 35:17.500
Everyone except
the penthouse level.

35:17.500 --> 35:19.120
The fumes are still
pretty bad up there,

35:19.120 --> 35:20.830
and it should really air out
for a few days.

35:20.830 --> 35:22.790
-Ben.
-Plastic in the oven.

35:22.790 --> 35:23.790
See it all the time.

35:23.790 --> 35:26.040
Bad smoke but no fire.

35:26.040 --> 35:28.670
Who put plastic
in the oven?

35:28.670 --> 35:30.120
Sometimes the trays
look like metal.

35:30.120 --> 35:31.710
Think it might've been
egg rolls.

35:31.710 --> 35:33.170
Man: You've got access?

35:33.170 --> 35:34.830
We don't know that
that was us.

35:34.830 --> 35:36.210
We're pretty sure it was.

35:36.210 --> 35:37.710
[ Indistinct shouting ]

35:37.710 --> 35:39.540
-Mer!
-Yeah?

35:39.540 --> 35:41.500
Meredith Grey...I want you
to meet my mother, Helen.

35:42.920 --> 35:46.830
Helen.
It's so nice to meet you.

35:46.830 --> 35:49.790
Meredith...
you're Alex's best friend.

35:49.790 --> 35:51.960
I am. And he's mine.

35:51.960 --> 35:55.380
♪♪

35:55.380 --> 35:56.540
That smoke is messing
with my eyes.

35:56.540 --> 35:57.580
Let's go.
Come on. Come on.

35:57.580 --> 35:59.960
[ Chuckling ]
Good night.

35:59.960 --> 36:02.000
[ Cellphone chimes ]

36:02.000 --> 36:04.210
Oh.

36:04.210 --> 36:06.710
Amelia doesn't need to
stay at my house now.

36:06.710 --> 36:08.210
Oh.
[ Engine revs in distance ]

36:08.210 --> 36:09.540
But maybe we should
go to your house

36:09.540 --> 36:11.250
just in case she changes
her mind again.

36:11.250 --> 36:12.460
Yeah.
Okay.

36:12.460 --> 36:14.330
[ Siren wails in distance ]

36:14.330 --> 36:15.790
[ Thunder rumbling ]

36:15.790 --> 36:18.750
I didn't mean
to be ungrateful.

36:18.750 --> 36:20.580
But you know how hard
this is for me, baby.

36:20.580 --> 36:23.120
It's hard for everyone.

36:23.120 --> 36:27.080
I know I wasn't the one that
was sick, but it was hell.

36:27.080 --> 36:29.670
You're not the only one who gets
to have feelings, you know?

36:29.670 --> 36:33.250
♪♪

36:33.250 --> 36:36.170
Unfortunate way
to meet the neighbors.

36:36.170 --> 36:38.170
Hey, we still have
the limo.

36:38.170 --> 36:40.790
We could all go
somewhere together.

36:40.790 --> 36:42.330
And celebrate.

36:42.330 --> 36:48.620
♪♪

36:48.620 --> 36:50.170
[ Laughs ]

36:52.500 --> 36:56.290
Uh, you're going to see
a very expensive blender

36:56.290 --> 36:57.750
on our next credit-card
statement.

36:57.750 --> 36:59.170
Because I deserve it.

36:59.170 --> 37:01.750
And I need a ride home.

37:01.750 --> 37:03.170
There's plenty of room
in the aid car.

37:03.170 --> 37:04.460
Oh.

37:04.460 --> 37:06.620
Um, and you can wear
this uniform home

37:06.620 --> 37:08.330
anytime you feel like it.

37:08.330 --> 37:11.880
Well, I think I'm gonna need to,
'cause, uh, you are fire.

37:11.880 --> 37:13.080
[ Laughs ]

37:15.420 --> 37:17.080
Ooh!

37:17.080 --> 37:19.620
This Kiki person sounds
like a real piece of work.

37:19.620 --> 37:21.670
She is.
[ Exhales sharply ]

37:21.670 --> 37:23.080
That's all right.
I'm gonna tell my story louder.

37:23.080 --> 37:24.880
I'm gonna start
my own fire.

37:24.880 --> 37:26.040
Mnh-mnh.
[ Laughs ]

37:26.040 --> 37:27.580
Let's come up with
a new metaphor, huh, babe?

37:27.580 --> 37:28.880
[ Laughs ]

37:28.880 --> 37:30.750
Am I just drunk,
or is this burger amazing?

37:30.750 --> 37:33.500
Everything tastes better
in the back of a limousine.

37:33.500 --> 37:34.620
-[ Laughs ]
-And you may also be drunk.

37:34.620 --> 37:35.920
[ Laughs ]

37:35.920 --> 37:38.210
Okay. From here on out...

37:40.210 --> 37:43.540
From here on out,
every scan that I get,

37:43.540 --> 37:45.120
good news or bad,

37:45.120 --> 37:49.170
this is how I want
to celebrate.

37:49.170 --> 37:52.290
In the back of my limousine,
eating trashy food,

37:52.290 --> 37:56.580
drinking expensive champagne
and sparkling apple cider.

37:56.580 --> 38:00.540
With the people that I love most
in this world.

38:00.540 --> 38:01.920
-Mwah!
-Mwah!

38:01.920 --> 38:03.040
Cheers to that.

38:03.040 --> 38:05.170
[ Laughs ]
Ah!

38:05.170 --> 38:08.380
Meredith: Surgeons are reluctant
to celebrate.

38:08.380 --> 38:10.250
Even in success,
we obsess about

38:10.250 --> 38:12.620
what could have been better.

38:12.620 --> 38:14.080
Whoa. What are you...

38:14.080 --> 38:15.710
Owen,
they brought Leo back.

38:15.710 --> 38:17.830
Why would they...
[ Door opens ]

38:17.830 --> 38:19.750
♪ I'm walking
on a thin line ♪

38:19.750 --> 38:21.170
-[ Fusses ]
-[ Exhales sharply ]

38:21.170 --> 38:22.460
♪ I try not to look down ♪

38:22.460 --> 38:23.620
Can we talk?

38:23.620 --> 38:25.000
[ Leo fusses ]

38:25.000 --> 38:28.420
♪ Can't stop my hands
from shaking ♪

38:28.420 --> 38:30.330
I mean, we fought her on it
at first.

38:30.330 --> 38:32.120
It just felt
so crazy for us to --

38:32.120 --> 38:35.170
giving up our grandchild,
but...

38:35.170 --> 38:38.380
We're gonna have our hands
so full with Britney,

38:38.380 --> 38:40.040
you know,
just helping her to adjust,

38:40.040 --> 38:42.420
to just stay sober and...

38:42.420 --> 38:45.540
Owen: Sure.
A-And we've seen
you with him and...

38:45.540 --> 38:47.380
You and Dr. Shepherd.

38:47.380 --> 38:50.670
And don't get me wrong, that
self-reflection is important.

38:50.670 --> 38:53.290
[ Voice breaking ] You brought
our Britney back to us.

38:53.290 --> 38:56.170
We're so grateful.

38:56.170 --> 38:58.210
And she always
just talks about

38:58.210 --> 39:00.920
you and Amelia
as being his parents.

39:00.920 --> 39:03.080
And she's right.

39:03.080 --> 39:04.290
♪ Wind upon the water ♪

39:04.290 --> 39:07.040
We're --
We're Britney's parents, but...

39:07.040 --> 39:08.880
♪ Storm under the sea ♪

39:08.880 --> 39:11.460
...you're Leo's.

39:11.460 --> 39:14.540
♪ 'Cause I know the moon's
watching over me ♪

39:14.540 --> 39:16.960
We only get better when
we admit our shortcomings,

39:16.960 --> 39:18.830
acknowledge our limits.

39:18.830 --> 39:21.500
[ Leo babbles ]

39:21.500 --> 39:23.620
[ Smooches ]
Yes, sweetheart.

39:23.620 --> 39:25.750
♪ What has been
will not always be ♪

39:25.750 --> 39:27.330
Are you sure
this is what you want?

39:27.330 --> 39:28.540
♪ Steady now ♪

39:28.540 --> 39:29.540
Yeah.

39:29.540 --> 39:30.790
♪ Eyes on the horizon ♪

39:30.790 --> 39:32.000
I want to be a kid.

39:32.000 --> 39:33.170
♪ This will pass ♪

39:33.170 --> 39:35.500
I-I want to be able
to make mistakes --

39:35.500 --> 39:39.500
You know, not, like,
overdose mistakes,

39:39.500 --> 39:41.830
but, like...
[ Inhales sharply ]

39:41.830 --> 39:43.500
...breaking curfew.

39:43.500 --> 39:46.920
Or, um, crashing my dad's car
into the fence.

39:46.920 --> 39:48.580
♪ Steady now ♪

39:48.580 --> 39:50.460
♪ Steady now ♪

39:50.460 --> 39:51.540
♪ Steady now ♪

39:51.540 --> 39:54.170
Thank you.

39:54.170 --> 39:55.500
For everything.

39:55.500 --> 39:59.920
♪♪

39:59.920 --> 40:02.170
So, um, you have our info.

40:02.170 --> 40:03.330
[ Leo coos ]
We do.

40:03.330 --> 40:04.920
Oh.

40:04.920 --> 40:06.750
♪♪

40:06.750 --> 40:07.750
Take care.

40:07.750 --> 40:11.710
And...keep in touch.

40:11.710 --> 40:14.500
But there are so many moments
along the way to celebrate.

40:14.500 --> 40:24.460
♪♪

40:24.460 --> 40:26.080
♪♪

40:26.080 --> 40:27.250
Bye.

40:27.250 --> 40:30.960
♪♪

40:30.960 --> 40:33.040
♪ Steady now ♪

40:33.040 --> 40:35.920
♪ Eyes on the horizon ♪

40:35.920 --> 40:37.580
♪ This will pass ♪

40:37.580 --> 40:39.040
♪ And the world
will keep spinning on ♪

40:39.040 --> 40:41.250
Some of those moments
are bigger than others.

40:41.250 --> 40:43.000
-Good night.
-Yes.

40:43.000 --> 40:44.580
♪ And on ♪

40:44.580 --> 40:51.000
♪♪

40:51.000 --> 40:52.620
[ Sighs ]

40:52.620 --> 40:54.120
♪♪

40:54.120 --> 40:56.420
♪ Steady now ♪

40:56.420 --> 40:58.540
And you really don't want
to miss those moments.

40:58.540 --> 41:00.580
So, yeah, I feel like
we missed some, um --

41:00.580 --> 41:02.120
[ Chuckles ]
Serious time together?

41:02.120 --> 41:03.500
[ Laughing ] Yeah.
Yeah.

41:03.500 --> 41:06.670
This is it.
[ Laughs ]

41:06.670 --> 41:09.580
Let me just, um,
get my -- out...
[ Keys jingle ]

41:09.580 --> 41:11.960
[ Vehicle approaches ]

41:11.960 --> 41:13.460
Hey, do you mind?

41:13.460 --> 41:15.500
Why you didn't
answer the phone?

41:15.500 --> 41:16.420
[ Engine shuts off ]

41:16.420 --> 41:17.790
What? Wha--

41:17.790 --> 41:20.080
Why --
What are you doing back?

41:20.080 --> 41:26.120
[ Conversing in Italian ]

41:38.670 --> 41:41.500
♪♪

41:41.500 --> 41:43.330
Because believe me
when I say...

41:43.330 --> 41:46.920
♪♪

41:46.920 --> 41:48.120
Andrea.

41:49.580 --> 41:51.460
I tried to warn you.

41:51.460 --> 41:54.790
Ciao! [ Laughs ]

41:54.790 --> 41:56.670
Uh. Uh...

41:56.670 --> 41:59.830
Ciao. Ciao.

41:59.830 --> 42:01.540
[ Chuckling ] Ciao.

42:01.540 --> 42:06.710
Um...M-Meredith,
this is, um, my dad.

42:06.710 --> 42:08.250
♪♪

42:08.250 --> 42:10.830
Oh. Buona sera.
Sera.

42:10.830 --> 42:15.000
...the bad times are gonna
find you all on their own.

42:15.000 --> 42:19.750
♪♪

42:28.210 --> 42:36.380
♪♪

42:36.380 --> 42:44.540
♪♪

42:44.540 --> 42:50.580
♪♪
